cmd_executor_tool.en:
【Unified Command Execution Tool】
Function: Supports executing shell commands/Shell scripts **locally/via SSH remotely** (must be supported by the openEuler operating system), automatically sets timeout time by command type, terminates execution automatically when timed out (Python native implementation, compatible with common commands and scripts), returns structured multilingual results

【Core Guidelines】
1. Command parameter (command) is required, empty value/None is not allowed;
2. Timeout parameter (timeout) is optional, if not passed, the default timeout time is automatically matched by command type; if passed, it must be a positive integer (unit: seconds), non-positive integers will automatically use the default value of 15 seconds;
3. Execution target parameter (host) is optional, **empty value/None/empty string/"None"/"null" are strictly prohibited**, default value is 127.0.0.1 (local execution); manually pass a remote host identifier (valid IP/hostname) only when SSH remote execution is needed, which will trigger SSH remote execution (remote host authentication information must be configured in advance); this parameter does not need to be filled in for local execution;
4. Mapping rules for command types and default timeout time (priority: user-specified timeout > Shell script command > normal command > global default):
   - Shell script commands (containing .sh, starting with bash / sh): default 600 seconds;
   - Long-time-consuming commands (yum/apt/docker/scp): 300/300/600/600 seconds respectively;
   - Medium-time-consuming commands (ping/curl): 30 seconds each;
   - Fast commands (ls/pwd/echo/cat/grep): 5/5/5/10/10 seconds respectively;
   - Unmatched commands: global default 15 seconds;
5. Command format requirement: Supports standard shell commands and Shell script paths (e.g., "/tmp/run.sh", "bash /root/install.sh"), which must be supported by the openEuler operating system; avoid execution failure caused by illegal commands;
6. Remote execution restrictions: For SSH remote execution, ensure that the local machine has configured the authentication information (account, password, port) of the target host, and the target host is an openEuler operating system;
7. Host parameter valid value constraints: Only valid IPv4 addresses (e.g., 127.0.0.1, 192.168.1.1) or valid hostnames (e.g., server01, openEuler-node) are allowed, empty value/None/special characters (e.g., *、!、@) are prohibited.

【Enum Class Definition (Must Follow)】
- CommandTimeoutEnum (Command Timeout Enum): LS=5 / PWD=5 / ECHO=5 / CAT=10 / GREP=10 / PING=30 / CURL=30 / YUM=300 / APT=300 / DOCKER=600 / SCP=600 / SHELL_SCRIPT=600 / DEFAULT=15
- LanguageEnum (Language Enum): ZH / EN
- HostValidTypeEnum (Host Valid Type Enum): IPV4 (e.g., 127.0.0.1), HOSTNAME (e.g., server01)

【Parameter Details】
- host: Execution target host identifier (optional, default 127.0.0.1 for local execution; fill in valid remote IP/hostname only for SSH remote execution, empty value/None prohibited; no need to fill in for local execution)
- command: Shell command/Shell script to execute (required, standard shell format, must be a command supported by openEuler)
- timeout: Execution timeout time (optional, positive integer, unit: seconds, default matched by command type)

【Return Value Explanation】
- success: Execution result (True=success, False=failure)
- message: Execution info/error prompt (multilingual, such as success, timeout, execution failure, remote authentication failure, host parameter illegal, etc.)
- result: Command execution result (returns command output content on success, empty string on failure/timeout)
- target: Execution target (127.0.0.1 for local, the passed host value for remote)
- timeout_used: The actual timeout time used (unit: seconds, convenient for troubleshooting timeout issues)
- original_host: The originally passed host value (convenient for troubleshooting parameter illegal issues)
